		<header>
			<h2><a href="/blog/madonna-song-to-tour/">PartyRock: Madonna Song-To-Tour Finder</a></h2>
			<h3>New York | Published <time>17 November 2023</time> in <a href="https://mariothomas.com/categories/aws/">AWS</a>  | 2 minute watch | <a href="/blog/madonna-song-to-tour/"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/link.svg" alt="Permalink" /></a></h3>
		</header>

		<p>Given <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamselipsky/">Adam&rsquo;s</a> announcement yesterday about <a href="https://partyrock.aws">Amazon PartyRock</a> powered by Amazon Bedrock, I decided I couldn&rsquo;t wait to get my hands on it and see what kind of app I could build.</p>

		<div id="AKJPG_wtjo8" onclick="loadYouTube(&#34;AKJPG_wtjo8&#34;)">
		<picture><source srcset="/blog/madonna-song-to-tour/img/madonna-song-to-tour-partyrock.webp" type="image/webp" alt="In this video, I built my first ever Amazon PartyRock app. You can enter any Madonna song name, and the app will tell you which tours Madonna has sung that song on." title="In this video, I built my first ever Amazon PartyRock app. You can enter any Madonna song name, and the app will tell you which tours Madonna has sung that song on." width="100%"><img src="/blog/madonna-song-to-tour/img/madonna-song-to-tour-partyrock.png" alt="In this video, I built my first ever Amazon PartyRock app. You can enter any Madonna song name, and the app will tell you which tours Madonna has sung that song on." title="In this video, I built my first ever Amazon PartyRock app. You can enter any Madonna song name, and the app will tell you which tours Madonna has sung that song on." width="100%">
		</picture>
		</div>

