			<h2><a href="https://www.ft.com/content/26d9f37b-bf22-4662-9fc8-1a1ae50011f3" target="_blank" title="Follow this link to read the article on FT.com">Generative AI: hype not hyperintelligence is lifting values</a></h2>
			<h3>Published <time>15 November 2023</time> in <a href="https://mariothomas.com/categories/generative-ai/">Generative AI</a>  | 10 minute read | <a href="/blog/ft-generative-ai-valuation/"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/link.svg" alt="Permalink" /></a>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ft.com/content/26d9f37b-bf22-4662-9fc8-1a1ae50011f3" target="_blank" title="Follow this link to read the article on FT.com"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/box-arrow-up-right.svg" alt="Follow this link to read the article on FT.com" /></a></h3>
		</header>

		
		Interesting read (pay-walled) in the FT on what&rsquo;s driving valuations in the generative AI space. The key to the adoption of any technology is finding the right investment case and quickly demonstrating proof of value. Generative AI is no different.
		
