	<article>

    	

		<header>
			<h2><a href="/blog/the-board-in-the-machine/">The Board in the machine</a></h2>
			<h3>Published <time>17 October 2022</time> in <a href="https://mariothomas.com/categories/board/">Board</a>  | 7 minute read | <a href="/blog/the-board-in-the-machine/"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/link.svg" alt="Permalink" /></a></h3>
		</header>

		
		<p>I recently hosted a fireside chat for the AWS Summit EMEA with Intel&rsquo; Global Leader for AI Solutions, Monica Livingston. We discussed how Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) are quickly becoming ubiquitous in business. The conversation prompted me to think about how Boards should be thinking about the use of AI and ML in their businesses, and how they need to ensure they are making the right decisions at the speed of light.</p>
		
		<footer>
